<1ST_LINE>d a PM-BRF--SlitThroat     03-12 0161</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Slit Throat,0165</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Defendant Slits Throat In Courtroom</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GREENSBURG, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 30-year-old man slit his throat with a
razor blade outside a judge's chambers shortly after being
convicted of sexually abusing a 7-year-old girl and repeatedly
burning her with a cigarette, authorities said.
   Albert John Lang of New Derry was in serious condition today at
Westmoreland Hospital in this western Pennsylvania city, said a
nursing supervisor who refused to give her name.
   The incident occurred Friday after Westmoreland County Judge
Daniel Ackerman excused the jury that convicted Lang, said District
Attorney John Driscoll.
   Lang was handing his personal belongings to his wife when he
suddenly charged toward Ackerman's door, Driscoll said. Deputy
sheriffs quickly locked the door.
   ``Lang then sliced his throat with a razor blade and was subdued
by the deputy sheriffs,'' Driscoll said.
   Lang was convicted of several counts of molestation and a charge
of wounding the girl 90 times with a cigarette, according to
Driscoll.
</TEXT>
