<DOCNO> AP880312-0019 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-03-12-88 0304EST</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r w BC-McFarlaneStatement     03-12 0333</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-McFarlane Statement,310</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>With PM-Iran-Contra Bjt</HEAD>
<HEAD>McFarlane's Statement On Guilty Plea</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Following is the text of Robert C. McFarlane's
statement to reporters after his guilty plea to misdemeanor charges
of misleading Congress in the Iran-Contra affair.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   I should say at the outset that from the beginning, Judge Walsh
and all of his staff have dealt with me in a thoroughly
professional way. As Judge Walsh has said, on the occasions that
were cited inside, I did indeed withhold information from the
Congress. I believe strongly that throughout, my actions were
motivated by what I believed was in the best foreign policy
interests of the United States.
   From the first moment when the Iran-Contra disclosures were made
in November of '86, I felt a profound personal obligation to
testify fully and voluntarily before the bodies that were formally
established to investigate this matter _ that includes the Tower
commission, the joint committee of the Congress, and the
independent counsel. I have done so, in more than 200 hours of
public and private testimony, without access to my records, or with
any request for or promise of immunity. I've told all that I know,
and it's on the public record for everyone to see. And I intend to
remain available to repeat it for as long as it's necessary to
bring this matter to a conclusion.
   I do think that it's unfortunate that the fundamental issue
here, that is, why congressional-executive relations broke down so
tragically, has not been and apparently cannot be dealt with by the
Congress or the courts. It seems to me important _ indeed,
imperative _ that an in-depth exploration of how to forge a better
working relationship is essential if the United States _ and I mean
by that the president and the Congress _ is to shoulder its global
leadership responsibility in the years ahead.
   And finally, I intend to do what I can to contribute to that
continuing effort.
</TEXT>
<HEAD>End of statement</HEAD>
</DOC>
