<1ST_LINE>d a PM-BRF--BankRobs     03-12 0134</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Bank Robs,0136</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Two Arrested in 21 Heist</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The arrest of two men is believed to have
solved 21 bank stick-ups committed in the last two months by a
motorcycle bandit and a robber dubbed ``The Old Man,'' police said.
   Mark MacAdoo, 22, of San Pedro, was arrested Thursday by FBI
agents and officers of the city police department's bank team while
awaiting a bus.
   MacAdoo was held in connection with 10 robberies in which the
bandit escaped on a motorcycle with a total of about $6,000, police
Lt. Bruce Meyer said Friday
   The second man, Howard Bonner, 59, nicknamed ``The Old Man''
because of his appearance, was arrested at a party Thursday night,
Meyer said. ``The Old Man'' stole about $20,000 in cash in 11
robberies, Meyer said.
</TEXT>
