to Michelob.''
   He said the average Soviet probably knows more about American
culture than Soviet culture, and that part of solving that
shortcoming lies in modern p.r. techniques.
   ``There is much we need to teach our own people, and much to
learn about accomplishing that,'' Kozitsyn said.
