<1ST_LINE>u i PM-StadiumStampede     03-12 0137</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Stadium Stampede,0140</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>URGENT</HEAD>
<HEAD>More Than 80 Reported Dead In Stadium Stampede</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KATMANDU, Nepal (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   More than 80 people were killed and
hundreds were injured today when soccer fans were trampled in a
stampede to get out of a hailstorm, eyewitnesses and hospital
sources said.
   The storm pelted about 30,000 fans with hailstones during a
match between a Nepalese and Bangladeshi team at the National
Stadium.
   Fans rushed to stadium exits but found them locked, witnesses
said.
   Hospital sources confirmed 60 dead and more than 250 injured,
many of them in critical condition. Witnesses said there were more
than 20 bodies left at the stadium that were not taken to hospitals.
   None of the athletes was involved in the stampede, they said.
   Strong winds accompanied the storm, uprooting trees in Katmandu
Valley, surrounding the capital.
</TEXT>
