<2ND_LINE>PM-Cyclone Deaths, 1st Ld - Writethru, a0500,0198</2ND_LINE>
<NOTE>EDS: SUBS 2nd graf, `Cyclone Filao...' with 1 graf to define
cyclone. Picks up 3rd, `The deaths...</NOTE>
<DATELINE>MAPUTO, Mozambique (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   At least 57 people were killed when a
cyclone hit the central coastal city of Quelimane earlier this
month, the national news agency AIM reported today.
   Cyclone Filao struck March 1 and damaged large parts of
Quelimane and surrounding rural areas, AIM reported. The word
cyclone is used in the Indian Ocean area to describe a hurricane.
   The deaths have not been reported previously due to poor
communications links, AIM said. The news agency said the death toll
may rise when information from surrounding areas becomes available.
   The cyclone destroyed 800 homes in Quelimane and neighboring
areas, leaving an estimated 4,000 people homeless, AIM said. Local
rice fields were damagaed and a government warehouse containing
food supplies was destroyed, AIM said.
   Large trees and telephone poles were ripped from the ground, and
parts of the city of about 75,000 remain without electricity, the
news agency said.
   Eduardo Joao, planning director for Zambezia province, estimated
the damage to buildings at just under $1 million.
</TEXT>
