<HEAD>Court Releases Ex-Police Chief In Torture-Death Case</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A former national police chief,
convicted of involvement in the torture death of a student
dissident, was released Saturday after his eight-month prison
sentence was suspended.
   The Seoul District Criminal Court found Kang Min-chang guilty of
