<HEAD>Couple That Won Car Risk Exorbitant Taxes</HEAD>
<DATELINE>STOCKHOLM, Sweden (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Mats and Margareta Johansson won a car
worth $10,000 on a TV game show, but the couple found out they may
have to pay $8,300 in taxes on the prize, a newspaper said Saturday.
   The newspaper Aftonbladet said the Johanssons took it for
granted that Ford Fiesta was a tax-free prize. They won it last
fall on the popular quiz game, ``The Card is Played,'' on Sweden's
publicly-owned television.
   The report said the couple was seeking exemption from tax on the
prize with the National Swedish Tax Board.
   Sweden's taxes are among the highest in the world and can take a
bite of 70 percent to 80 percent of earnings on an average salary.
