<1ST_LINE>r a AM-BakkerHouse     03-12 0332</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Bakker House,0341</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Bakker House for Sale for Just Under a Million Dollars</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TEGA CAY, S.C. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Jim and Tammy Bakker's PTL-owned
five-level house will be put on the auction block on April 12, with
the minimum price set at $995,000.
   The money will go to help the PTL ministry based in nearby Fort
Mill pay its debts.
   Dave Huneycutt of Lake Wylie Realtors said he's had about 55
inquiries about the house since the auction notice appeared
Tuesday. They include ``doctors, lawyers, well-known sports
promoters and very successful independent business people,'' he
said.
   The 10,226-square-foot house was built in 1976 and enlarged four
times after PTL bought it in 1981 as a parsonage for the Bakkers
and their two children.
   The master bedroom has his and hers bathroom suites, connected
by a sunken whirlpool tub. The tub is flanked by a glass-enclosed
rock garden. Faucet handles are in the shape of long-neck swans.
   The Bakkers apparently shared a 600-square-foot carpeted clothes
closet that adjoined her dressing room. Large mirrors abound _ in
the music room, the exercise room, the bathrooms and other areas.
   The house has a commercial kitchen with heavy-duty appliances,
two additional kitchens and at least 25 closets. Electronically
controlled draperies and curtains are in most major rooms,
including his study and the master bedroom.
   The massive house sits at the bottom of a steep hill and fronts
Lake Wylie in one of Tega Cay's most exclusive sections.
   The grounds include a two-story playhouse that is heated and
air-conditioned, a guardhouse, boardwalks to a white sandy beach at
the water's edge, and a large dock where the Bakkers once kept
their 58-foot houseboat and small power cruiser.
   The Bakkers left the home last June, three months after Bakker
admitted to a 1980 sexual encounter with church secretary Jessica
Hahn and resigned.
   The Bakker home is one of 10 PTL properties that will be sold
April 12 at the Tega Cay Country Club, according to auctioneer
Rodney Robinson.
</TEXT>
