<DATELINE>PANAMA CITY, Panama (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Panamanians who have been unable to
cash their checks for 10 days faced cuts in public services today
as Washington increased economic pressure on the government to
force Panama's strongman to resign.
   President Reagan on Friday froze millions of dollars in
Panamanian assets in the United States and again called on Gen.
Manuel Antonio Noriega to step down as chief of the 15,000-member
Defense Forces.
   Reagan said he is prepared to take additional steps against
