<2ND_LINE>BC-Sweden-Merger,0111</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Second Major Forestry Takeover Attempt In A Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>STOCKHOLM, Sweden (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   One of Sweden's largest lumber
companies, Mo-och Domsjo AB, offered $1.03 billion Friday for two
pulp and paper concerns, the second major takeover attempt in
Sweden's forestry business this week.
   MoDo's offer for Holmens Bruk AB and Iggesunds AB came two days
after Stora AB, Sweden's largest forestry products group, offered
$1 billion for Swedish Match AB.
   Bernt Lof, MoDo's chief executive, said the offer consisted of
$101 million in cash and the rest in securities. A successful
takeover would create one of the world's largest makers of
newsprint and writing paper.
</TEXT>
