<1ST_LINE>d f AM-ValuableFish     03-12 0138</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Valuable Fish,0142</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>New Bedford Fishermen Haul in $143 Million in 1987</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW BEDFORD, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fishermen in New Bedford hauled in
$143.7 million worth of scallops and fish last year, which
virtually locks the city's title as the most lucrative U.S. fishing
port, officials said Friday.
   The catch of 76.3 million pounds is expected to be the most
valuable in the nation for the fifth straight year, said Jay Tebeau
of the National Marine Fisheries Service. The value of the 1987
catch was a 26 percent increase over 1986.
   The service annually ranks about 60 U.S. ports according to
dollar value and pounds of seafood. Figures for other ports will
not be available for weeks, but Tebeau said, ``It's a sure bet that
New Bedford will come in tops as far as value is concerned.''
</TEXT>
